Rakuen's Canopy Workshop compact has practical access to Confluence Text sections through its
retained Circle-lineage Sorcerer practitioners. The sections most relevant to Rakuen's disaster
management—atmospheric interaction during ashfall events, water-earth multi-school boundary
effects during flood conditions, and vegetation-fire interaction in forest-adjacent burn scenarios—
are maintained in working form by the retained practitioners as operational reference rather
than scholarly archive. Rakuen has no Axiomatic academic institutional presence of its own and
therefore no formal restriction on Confluence Text access. The Garden Ledger Clerks' archive
contains references to Confluence Text consultations during two of the four southern grain
emergencies in the last sixty years; both cases involved synthesis approaches that single-school
analysis could not have provided.

flags MAFDET
