Rivennid crystal-preservation enchantment embeds Conclave-era preservation magic in biological
substrate—itself a multi-school synthesis effect that the Confluence Texts document under
"persistent cross-domain binding in biological medium." Rivennid practitioners who study the
relevant Confluence Text sections find detailed documentation of the interaction effects they
experience as native cognition. The crystal-resonance that runs through Rivennid biology
amplifies their engagement with synthesis-oriented arcane practice; the Texts provide the
external theoretical framework for what Rivennid already perceive through their network
connection. Rivennid scholars have contributed observations to Confluence Text-lineage research
through the Kiess independent scholarly network—specifically observations of the Blightmother's
interaction effects with the surrounding forest ecosystem, which display multi-school dynamics
at ecological scale that the Texts' existing framework does not fully capture.
